<html>
  <problem>
    <img src="/static/problems/MIT/boriskor/BKimages/17-two connected satellites.png" alt="Two satellites connected by a string revolve in concentric circular orbits" encrypturl="no"/>
    <parameter default="2" description="Maximum Number of Tries" type="int_pos" name="maxtries" loncapaid="11"/>
    <br/>
    
      <p>
Two satellites of equal masses \(m\) revolve around the planet of mass \(M\) (M&gt;&gt;m). The radii of the orbits of the satellites are \(r\) and \(2r\). The satellites are connected by a light string, directed along the radius of the orbit, that keeps their periods of revolution equal. Find the force of tension in the string. </p>
    
    <br/>
    <multiplechoiceresponse max="10" direction="vertical" randomize="yes" loncapaid="12" type="MultipleChoice">
      <choicegroup type="MultipleChoice">
        <choice location="random" name="foil1" correct="true">

                \(F_T = (7/12)GMm/r^2\)
          
        </choice>
        <choice location="random" name="foil2" correct="false">

                \(F_T = (3/5)GMm/r^2\)
          
        </choice>
        <choice location="random" name="foil3" correct="false">

                \(F_T = (5/3)GMm/r^2\)
          
        </choice>
        <choice location="random" name="foil4" correct="false">

                \(F_T = 2GMm/r^2\)
          
        </choice>
        <choice location="random" name="foil5" correct="false">

                \(F_T = (3/2)GMm/r^2\)
          
        </choice>
      </choicegroup>
    </multiplechoiceresponse>
      </problem>
</html>
